snippet.title: Sezen Aksu - Biliyorsun (Official Audio)
snippet.description:
Hayat bazen öyle insafsız ki 
Küçük bir boşluğundan yakalar 
Hissettirmez en zayıf anında 
Seni ta yüreğinden yaralar 

Ellerin kolların bağlansada 
Başında kasırgalar kopsada 
Sen tüm gücünle karşı koysanda 
Seni acımasız sevdaya salar 

Sende benim kadar gerçekleri görüyorsun 
Beraber olamayız benim gibi biliyorsun 
Bir başka dünyanın insanısın yavrucağım 
Sen kendi dünyanın toprağında büyüyorsun 

Haklısın biraz geç karşılaştık 
Oysa hiç konuşmadan anlaştık 
Bazı şeyler var ki söylenmiyor 
Biz senle sözleri susarak aştık 

İnsan acılarla kıvransa da 
Ve o aşkta bir daha doğsa da 
Dünyasını yeniden kursa da 
Düşler ve gerçekler ayrı ayrı yaşar 

Sende benim kadar gerçekleri görüyorsun 
Beraber olamayız benim gibi biliyorsun 
Bir başka dünyanın insanısın yavrucağım 
Sen kendi dünyanın toprağında büyüyorsun

Söz : Sezen Aksu
Beste : Sezen Aksu
Düzenleme : Attila Özdemiroğlu

=============================

Sezen Aksu Resmi YouTube Kanalına Abone Olun: https://goo.gl/xPnZlA

=================================

=================================

Rally the Veilguard and defy the gods in Dragon Age: The Veilguard, coming fall 2024
 
Learn more: https://www.ea.com/games/dragon-age/dragon-age-the-veilguard

snippet.title: Gracie Abrams - Where do we go now? (Live Performance) | Vevo
snippet.description:
Gracie Abrams - Where do we go now?. An exclusive live performance for Vevo. 

Gracie Abrams and Vevo first crossed paths when we captured a couple cozy DSCVR performances from her backyard during the pandemic. Matter of fact, that was some of her first performance content ever. We were high on the smoky-voiced singer-songwriter from the jump, before her first live shows, before she gave her ‘This Is What It Feels Like’ EP to the world, before her Insta followers jumped from a perfectly impressive 300k to an undeniable 1.8 million. All those things are intertwined, by the way. Her legion of fans now hang on every note at packed shows. And oh yeah, talent knows talent; Gracie's been warming up stadium stages for Taylor Swift of late, an incomparable spotlight moment for the indie guitar tenderness heard on Abrams' debut album, ‘Good Riddance,’ which arrived in Feb and just got a deluxe update. Be warned before you dive into “Where do we go now?” and “Fault line.” Those lush waves of indecision and anxiety that she controls with quiet gravity can drag you into an emotional rip current before you know it. In that case, best to let go.

Watch Gracie Abrams music videos:
https://bit.ly/32KhiYo

snippet.title: Gracie Abrams - Where do we go now? (Live Performance) | Vevo
snippet.description:
Gracie Abrams - Where do we go now?. An exclusive live performance for Vevo. 

Gracie Abrams and Vevo first crossed paths when we captured a couple cozy DSCVR performances from her backyard during the pandemic. Matter of fact, that was some of her first performance content ever. We were high on the smoky-voiced singer-songwriter from the jump, before her first live shows, before she gave her ‘This Is What It Feels Like’ EP to the world, before her Insta followers jumped from a perfectly impressive 300k to an undeniable 1.8 million. All those things are intertwined, by the way. Her legion of fans now hang on every note at packed shows. And oh yeah, talent knows talent; Gracie's been warming up stadium stages for Taylor Swift of late, an incomparable spotlight moment for the indie guitar tenderness heard on Abrams' debut album, ‘Good Riddance,’ which arrived in Feb and just got a deluxe update. Be warned before you dive into “Where do we go now?” and “Fault line.” Those lush waves of indecision and anxiety that she controls with quiet gravity can drag you into an emotional rip current before you know it. In that case, best to let go.
